"title": "1165: God, uniqueness of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1165",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>No-one and nothing is comparable to the triune God in his nature or comparable to him in his character and activity.</p>\n<h2>There is no God except the LORD</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:5-Isa45:6\">ISA 45:5–45:6</a></strong> <em>God alone stands outside nature as its Creator. All other beings are created by him.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:35\">DEU 4:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:4\">DEU 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:3\">DEU 32:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:60\">1KI 8:60</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps83:18\">PSA 83:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:10\">PSA 86:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:10-Isa43:11\">ISA 43:10–43:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:6-Isa44:8\">ISA 44:6–44:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:18\">ISA 45:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:4-1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:4–8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:6\">EPH 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5\">1TI 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>There is no-one like God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:6-Ps89:8\">PSA 89:6–89:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:10\">EXO 8:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:18\">ISA 40:18</a></p>\n<h3>In his creative power</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:25-Isa40:26\">ISA 40:25–40:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:3\">JHN 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:6\">NEH 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:15\">ACT 14:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16\">COL 1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:11\">REV 4:11</a></p>\n<h3>In his mighty acts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:10\">PSA 86:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:5-Ps135:6\">PSA 135:5–135:6</a></p>\n<h3>In his character and glory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:11\">EXO 15:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:22\">2SA 7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:11\">1CH 29:11</a></p>\n<h3>In his ability to save</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:26\">DEU 33:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:20-Isa45:22\">ISA 45:20–45:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:5-Jer10:6\">JER 10:5–10:6</a></p>\n<h3>In his covenant love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:23\">1KI 8:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:22-2Sam7:23\">2SA 7:22–7:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:20-1Chr17:21\">1CH 17:20–17:21</a></p>\n<h3>In his sovereignty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:9\">ZEC 14:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:39\">DEU 4:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a></p>\n<h2>Implications of God's uniqueness</h2>\n<h3>God alone is to be worshipped</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:2-Exod20:3\">EXO 20:2–20:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:6-Deut5:7\">DEU 5:6–5:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:13\">EXO 23:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:24\">EXO 23:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:4\">LEV 19:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13-Deut6:14\">DEU 6:13–6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:35\">2KI 17:35</a></p>\n<h3>Idolatry is empty and worthless</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:8\">JON 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:28\">DEU 4:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:18-Isa44:20\">ISA 44:18–44:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:20\">ISA 45:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:18\">HAB 2:18</a></p>",
